IS  - 8
SP  - 1954
EP  - 1970
PY  - 2011
DA  - 2011/08/01/
SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jbankfin.2011.01.003
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0378426611000240
KW  - Asymmetric correlation
KW  - Asymmetric dependence
KW  - Copula
KW  - Tail dependence
KW  - GARCH
KW  - Regime switching
AB  - Common negative extreme variations in returns are prevalent in international equity markets. This has been widely documented with statistical tools such as exceedance correlation, extreme value theory, and Gaussian bivariate GARCH or regime-switching models. We point to limits of these tools to characterize extreme dependence and propose an alternative regime-switching copula model that includes one normal regime in which dependence is symmetric and a second regime characterized by asymmetric dependence. We apply this model to international equity and bond markets, to allow for inter-market movements. Empirically, we find that dependence between international assets of the same type is strong in both regimes, especially in the asymmetric one, but weak between equities and bonds, even in the same country.
